  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6572.4 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6568, dealers are currently in positive gamma territory and likely buying this dip while providing natural support - the massive GEX surge (22.7% 1-min) suggests heavy options flow is forcing aggressive dealer rebalancing. The thick wall of positive gamma from 6575-6600 (especially the 45.2B at 6580) will act as strong resistance where dealers will aggressively sell any rallies, creating a natural ceiling and promoting mean reversion back toward the flip level. Watch 6568 as the critical pivot - below this dealers flip to negative gamma and become destabilizing momentum sellers, while above 6580 expect heavy dealer selling pressure into that massive gamma wall.",
